## 🔹 Q7: `key` Prop Re‑render Behavior

```jsx
function Counter({ count }) {
  React.useEffect(() => {
    console.log("Mounted");
  }, []);

  return <h1>{count}</h1>;
}

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = React.useState(0);
  return (
    <>
      <Counter key={count} count={count} />
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>+</button>
    </>
  );
}
```

### ✅ Output (on every button click)

    Mounted

### ✅ Explanation

*   Changing `key` unmounts & remounts component
*   Effect runs every time

