## 🔹 Q9: React Batching (Interview Favorite)

```jsx
function App() {
  const [n, setN] = React.useState(0);

  const handleClick = () => {
    setN(n + 1);
    console.log(n);
    setTimeout(() => {
      console.log(n);
    }, 0);
  };

  return <button onClick={handleClick}>Click</button>;
}
```

### ✅ Output

    0
    0

### ✅ Explanation

*   Closure captures old value
*   `setTimeout` doesn't get updated state

