## 🧨 Q10: `useEffect` Dependency Identity

```jsx
function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = React.useState(0);

  const obj = { value: count };

  React.useEffect(() => {
    console.log("effect");
  }, [obj]);

  return <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>+</button>;
}
```

### ✅ Output (on every render)

